<p>I am conflicted about this tale. The resurrection cannon does feature the revival of old characters and whatnot, but usually that uses old tales as a basis for the new ones, flowering off in a different direction and exploring the aftershocks years later. Kondraki's destruction of site 19 is already set in stone. However, this story is more of a rehash/rewrite over a new addition, and takes place before/during the Kondraki+682's rampage. It is certainly competently written, but no vote for now.</p>

							</div>

								
					
